I found a solution to the uninstall problem.

there's a folder in the installer files called "Groove.en-us". Take the Setup.xml file located there and copy it to:

C:/Program Files/Common Files/microsoft shared/OFFICE14/Office Setup Controller/Groove.en-us/

Try running the uninstaller again, and it should work.

SOLUTION FOR UNINSTALL ISSUE:

If you double-click on the uninstaller in the control panel window, and receive an error message telling you to run setup again from the source, do the following:

1. While the error window is open, launch task manager
2. locate the setup.exe file, right click, and select ?Open File Location? ? this will take you to the local installation folder
3. Close the error dialog box and simply copy your installation files from your CD or other folder into this one, replacing any files
4. Re-run the uninstaller from the control panel

Voila! Uninstallation proceeds as expected.
